Layer 1: Browser → Boomi
D365 gets a user MSAL token (api://<ApiAppId>/access_as_user).
Sent to Boomi as Authorization: Bearer <user-token> plus x-api-key.
Boomi uses this to confirm who signed in at the gateway.
Layer 2: Boomi → Function
Boomi does not forward the user’s bearer token to the Function.
Boomi gets its own token via client credentials (api://<ApiAppId>/.default).
That token carries app roles (Contact.Read for EApp, Policy.Read for Policy).
Easy Auth on the Function validates that token.
